Transitions of Kafka cluster statuses. Where :
10 - DOWN;
6 - DEGRADED;
0 - UP.

Transitions of controller broker states. The controller changes state when processing an event. Most of the time, the Idle state is displayed, which means that the controller has processed all the events. If the event processing takes a considerable time (several seconds or more), this state of the controller will be displayed. Where:
16 - Update Metadata Response Received;
15 - List Partition Reassignment;
14 - Topic Unclean Leader Election Enable;
13 - Unclean Leader Election Enable;
12 - Controller Shutdown;
11 - Log Dir Change;
10 - Leader And Isr Response Received;
9 - Isr Change;
8 - Controlled Shutdown;
7 - Manual Leader Balance;
6 - Auto Leader Balance;
5 - Alter Partition Reassignment;
4 - Topic Deletion;
3 - Topic Change;
2 - Broker Change;
1 - Controller Change;
0 - Idle.
